This paper proposes a method for facial expression recognition using deep learning and 4D data. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.CV and cs.MM sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which falls under the cs.LG sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed method in human-computer interaction, which is covered in the cs.HC sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of data augmentation techniques to improve performance, which is a common topic in the cs.NE sub-category.
